<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="446" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1266,2020]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1266,1291]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Only female known. The species is characteristic in having four dark patches on the scutum, eyes narrowly separated; the proximal half of the 
<number box="[676,690,1305,1330]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="5.0">5</number>
th tarsal segments bearing ventral patch of dense, short, hair-like setae. The female of 
<taxonomicName authority="Clastrier, 1988" authorityName="Clastrier" authorityYear="1988" box="[386,750,1341,1366]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Afrostilobezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornatithorax">
<emphasis box="[386,403,1342,1365]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[417,558,1341,1365]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">ornatithorax</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Clastrier" box="[573,741,1341,1366]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" refString="Clastrier, J. (1988) Description de cinq nouveaux Stilobezzia de la Republique de Guinee (Diptera, Ceratopogonidae). Nouvelle Revue d'Entomologie, New Series, 5, 121 - 132." type="journal article" year="1988">
Clastrier, 
<number box="[684,741,1342,1366]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="1988.0">1988</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is smaller and differs in having only two dark patches on the scutum, unmodified 
<number box="[384,398,1380,1405]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="5.0">5</number>
th tarsal segments, a mandible armed with 
<number box="[877,891,1380,1405]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="6.0">6</number>
coarse teeth, and very narrowly separated eyes, almost touching above the antennae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="448" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1266,2020]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,320]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="447" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1452,1477]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Description.</emphasis>
Female. Body yellowish brown, with 
<number box="[787,801,1453,1477]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="4.0">4</number>
dark brown lateral patches on scutum (
<figureCitation box="[1258,1327,1452,1477]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1725,1747]" captionTargetBox="[190,1402,193,1706]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[190,1402,193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Afrostilobezzia clastrieri sp. nov., holotype female: a—thorax, lateral view; b—anterior lateral cervical sclerite, lateral view; c, d—palisade setae on hind leg basitarsus (indicated with arrows); e—tibial comb of hind leg; f—tarsomeres 4 and 5 of fore leg, short hair-like setae indicated with arrow; g—inner barb of inner claw of fore leg (indicated with arrow); h—outer barb of inner claw of fore leg (indicated with arrow)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233805/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">
Fig. 
<number box="[1313,1327,1453,1477]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
a), darker postnotum and slightly darker dorsal surface of abdomen. Palpal segment 
<number box="[992,1006,1488,1513]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="5.0">5</number>
dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[1161,1230,1488,1513]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1442,1464]" captionTargetBox="[191,1403,176,1399]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[191,1403,159,1400]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Afrostilobezzia clastrieri sp. nov., holotype female: a—head, frontal view; b—flagellomere 2; c—terminal flagellomere; d—palpal segment 3; e—mandibles." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233804/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">
Fig. 
<number box="[1214,1230,1488,1512]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
a). Flagellum 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.52" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" unit="mm" value="2.52">2.52 mm</quantity>
long, longer than wing measured from basal arculus. First flagellomere without sensilla coeloconica. Terminal flagellomere with 
<number box="[358,372,1560,1584]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="2.0">2</number>
distinct apical sensilla basiconica. Antennal ratio AR 
<number box="[986,1038,1560,1585]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="1.06">1.06</number>
. Proportions of flagellomeres 
<number box="[1380,1436,1560,1584]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="7.0" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="1.0">1–13</number>
as follows (in mm): 
<number box="[377,440,1597,1621]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="0.247">0.247</number>
– 
<number box="[468,531,1596,1621]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="0.164">0.164</number>
– 
<number box="[558,712,1596,1621]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="0.1545" valueMax="0.156" valueMin="0.153">0.153 – 0.156</number>
– 
<number box="[739,802,1596,1621]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="0.157">0.157</number>
– 
<number box="[830,984,1596,1621]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="0.161" valueMax="0.166" valueMin="0.156">0.156 – 0.166</number>
– 
<number box="[1011,1164,1597,1621]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="0.208" valueMax="0.242" valueMin="0.174">0.174 – 0.242</number>
– 
<number box="[1192,1255,1596,1621]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="0.246">0.246</number>
– 
<number box="[1283,1436,1596,1621]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="0.2475" valueMax="0.253" valueMin="0.242">0.242 – 0.253</number>
– 
<number box="[175,238,1632,1657]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="0.305">0.305</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[256,328,1632,1657]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1913,1935]" captionTargetBox="[188,1399,375,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[188,1400,375,1889]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrostilobezzia clastrieri sp. nov., holotype female: a—wing, b—flagellomeres 6 – 13, c—mandible, d—tarsomere 5 of fore leg, lateral view, e—maxillary palp, lateral view, f—seminal capsules." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233803/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">
Figs 
<number box="[317,328,1632,1657]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
b, 
<number box="[362,377,1632,1657]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="2.0">2</number>
b–c). Mandible armed with 
<number box="[702,743,1632,1656]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7–8</number>
coarse teeth decreasing in size apically (
<figureCitation box="[1224,1297,1632,1657]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1913,1935]" captionTargetBox="[188,1399,375,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[188,1400,375,1889]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrostilobezzia clastrieri sp. nov., holotype female: a—wing, b—flagellomeres 6 – 13, c—mandible, d—tarsomere 5 of fore leg, lateral view, e—maxillary palp, lateral view, f—seminal capsules." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233803/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">
Figs 
<number box="[1285,1297,1632,1656]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
c, 
<number box="[1329,1345,1632,1656]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="2.0">2</number>
e). Eyes narrowly separated, by 
<number box="[415,450,1668,1693]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="0.6">0.6</number>
times the width of an ommatidial facet. Transverse interocular suture over vertical seta present (
<figureCitation box="[251,323,1704,1729]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1442,1464]" captionTargetBox="[191,1403,176,1399]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[191,1403,159,1400]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Afrostilobezzia clastrieri sp. nov., holotype female: a—head, frontal view; b—flagellomere 2; c—terminal flagellomere; d—palpal segment 3; e—mandibles." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233804/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">
Fig. 
<number box="[307,323,1704,1728]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
a). Palpus 
<number box="[446,458,1704,1729]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="5.0">5</number>
-segmented (
<figureCitation box="[609,676,1704,1729]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1913,1935]" captionTargetBox="[188,1399,375,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[188,1400,375,1889]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrostilobezzia clastrieri sp. nov., holotype female: a—wing, b—flagellomeres 6 – 13, c—mandible, d—tarsomere 5 of fore leg, lateral view, e—maxillary palp, lateral view, f—seminal capsules." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233803/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">
Fig. 
<number box="[665,676,1704,1728]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
e). Third palpal segment slender, length 
<quantity box="[1154,1273,1704,1728]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.17" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" unit="mm" value="0.117">0.117 mm</quantity>
, with shallow sensory pit located on apical 
<number box="[476,486,1741,1765]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[497,511,1741,1765]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="3.0">3</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[526,594,1740,1765]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1913,1935]" captionTargetBox="[188,1399,375,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[188,1400,375,1889]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrostilobezzia clastrieri sp. nov., holotype female: a—wing, b—flagellomeres 6 – 13, c—mandible, d—tarsomere 5 of fore leg, lateral view, e—maxillary palp, lateral view, f—seminal capsules." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233803/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">
Figs 
<number box="[583,594,1741,1765]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
e, 
<number box="[623,638,1740,1765]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="2.0">2</number>
d). Clypeus with 
<number box="[830,844,1740,1765]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="6.0">6</number>
long setae distributed laterally in two rows. Cervical sclerite slender, S-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[452,518,1776,1801]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1725,1747]" captionTargetBox="[190,1402,193,1706]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[190,1402,193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Afrostilobezzia clastrieri sp. nov., holotype female: a—thorax, lateral view; b—anterior lateral cervical sclerite, lateral view; c, d—palisade setae on hind leg basitarsus (indicated with arrows); e—tibial comb of hind leg; f—tarsomeres 4 and 5 of fore leg, short hair-like setae indicated with arrow; g—inner barb of inner claw of fore leg (indicated with arrow); h—outer barb of inner claw of fore leg (indicated with arrow)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233805/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">
Fig. 
<number box="[504,518,1776,1801]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
b). Wing length 
<quantity box="[702,805,1776,1800]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.39" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" unit="mm" value="2.39">2.39 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[888,991,1776,1800]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.7" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" unit="mm" value="0.77">0.77 mm</quantity>
, CR 
<number box="[1047,1100,1776,1801]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="0.85">0.85</number>
. Both first radial cells present (
<figureCitation box="[159,225,1812,1837]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1913,1935]" captionTargetBox="[188,1399,375,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[188,1400,375,1889]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrostilobezzia clastrieri sp. nov., holotype female: a—wing, b—flagellomeres 6 – 13, c—mandible, d—tarsomere 5 of fore leg, lateral view, e—maxillary palp, lateral view, f—seminal capsules." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233803/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">
Fig. 
<number box="[214,225,1813,1837]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
a). Second radial cell 
<number box="[480,515,1813,1837]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="3.1">3.1</number>
times longer than first one. Some macrotrichia at wing apex present. Scutellum bearing 
<number box="[243,257,1848,1873]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="6.0">6</number>
marginal setae. Coxae of all legs bearing strong setae (
<figureCitation box="[882,949,1848,1873]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1725,1747]" captionTargetBox="[190,1402,193,1706]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[190,1402,193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Afrostilobezzia clastrieri sp. nov., holotype female: a—thorax, lateral view; b—anterior lateral cervical sclerite, lateral view; c, d—palisade setae on hind leg basitarsus (indicated with arrows); e—tibial comb of hind leg; f—tarsomeres 4 and 5 of fore leg, short hair-like setae indicated with arrow; g—inner barb of inner claw of fore leg (indicated with arrow); h—outer barb of inner claw of fore leg (indicated with arrow)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233805/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">
Fig. 
<number box="[935,949,1848,1872]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
a), 
<number box="[985,999,1848,1872]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="8.0">8</number>
on fore, 
<number box="[1102,1130,1848,1872]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="10.0">10</number>
on mid, and 
<number box="[1280,1294,1848,1873]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="5.0">5</number>
on hind leg. 
<collectingCountry box="[151,207,1884,1909]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibial comb with 
<number box="[404,418,1885,1909]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="8.0">8</number>
spines (
<figureCitation box="[510,577,1884,1909]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1725,1747]" captionTargetBox="[190,1402,193,1706]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[190,1402,193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Afrostilobezzia clastrieri sp. nov., holotype female: a—thorax, lateral view; b—anterior lateral cervical sclerite, lateral view; c, d—palisade setae on hind leg basitarsus (indicated with arrows); e—tibial comb of hind leg; f—tarsomeres 4 and 5 of fore leg, short hair-like setae indicated with arrow; g—inner barb of inner claw of fore leg (indicated with arrow); h—outer barb of inner claw of fore leg (indicated with arrow)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233805/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">
Fig. 
<number box="[563,577,1885,1909]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
e). 
<collectingCountry box="[612,668,1884,1909]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibial spur short. 
<collectingCountry box="[865,921,1884,1909]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Hind</collectingCountry>
legs with tarsomeres 
<number box="[1165,1207,1885,1909]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
with three complete rows of palisade setae (
<figureCitation box="[412,482,1920,1945]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1725,1747]" captionTargetBox="[190,1402,193,1706]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[190,1402,193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Afrostilobezzia clastrieri sp. nov., holotype female: a—thorax, lateral view; b—anterior lateral cervical sclerite, lateral view; c, d—palisade setae on hind leg basitarsus (indicated with arrows); e—tibial comb of hind leg; f—tarsomeres 4 and 5 of fore leg, short hair-like setae indicated with arrow; g—inner barb of inner claw of fore leg (indicated with arrow); h—outer barb of inner claw of fore leg (indicated with arrow)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233805/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">
Figs 
<number box="[469,482,1920,1945]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
c–d). First tarsomere of fore leg with 
<number box="[903,946,1920,1945]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
strong spines on proximal half. Tarsomeres 
<number box="[151,193,1957,1981]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
of mid leg armed with 
<number box="[476,490,1957,1981]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="2.0">2</number>
distinct apical spines, in addition first tarsomere bearing 
<number box="[1162,1176,1957,1981]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="3.0">3</number>
ventral spines. Fourth tarsomere cordiform. Fifth tarsomere armed with two almost equal claws. Proximal half of 
<number box="[1198,1212,1995,2020]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" value="5.0">5</number>
th tarsomere bearing ventral patch of dense, short, hair like setae (
<figureCitation box="[648,715,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1913,1935]" captionTargetBox="[188,1399,375,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[188,1400,375,1889]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrostilobezzia clastrieri sp. nov., holotype female: a—wing, b—flagellomeres 6 – 13, c—mandible, d—tarsomere 5 of fore leg, lateral view, e—maxillary palp, lateral view, f—seminal capsules." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233803/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">
Figs 
<number box="[704,715,151,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
d, 
<number box="[745,759,151,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="3.0">3</number>
f). Claws strongly bent at the base, inner one with very small outer and inner barb at basal 
<number box="[478,488,188,212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[499,513,188,212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="3.0">3</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[529,597,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1913,1935]" captionTargetBox="[188,1399,375,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[188,1400,375,1889]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrostilobezzia clastrieri sp. nov., holotype female: a—wing, b—flagellomeres 6 – 13, c—mandible, d—tarsomere 5 of fore leg, lateral view, e—maxillary palp, lateral view, f—seminal capsules." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233803/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">
Figs 
<number box="[586,597,188,213]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
d, 
<quantity box="[628,656,188,213]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" unit="g" value="3.0">3g</quantity>
–h). Tarsal ratio of legs as follows: 
<collectingCountry box="[1054,1093,188,212]" name="Chile" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">TR</collectingCountry>
(I) 
<number box="[1125,1163,188,212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="2.3">2.3</number>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1174,1212,188,212]" name="Chile" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">TR</collectingCountry>
(II) 
<number box="[1255,1293,188,212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="2.9">2.9</number>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1304,1342,188,212]" name="Chile" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">TR</collectingCountry>
(III) 
<number box="[1394,1432,188,212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="2.2">2.2</number>
. Two unequal, ovoid, short-necked, functional seminal capsules present (
<figureCitation box="[956,1015,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1913,1935]" captionTargetBox="[188,1399,375,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[188,1400,375,1889]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrostilobezzia clastrieri sp. nov., holotype female: a—wing, b—flagellomeres 6 – 13, c—mandible, d—tarsomere 5 of fore leg, lateral view, e—maxillary palp, lateral view, f—seminal capsules." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233803/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">
Fig. 
<number box="[1005,1015,223,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
f), both with surface pores; respective length/width proportions as follows: 
<number box="[569,631,260,285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="0.097">0.097</number>
/ 
<quantity box="[640,755,260,285]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.4" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" unit="mm" value="0.054">0.054 mm</quantity>
and 
<number box="[812,875,260,284]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="0.084">0.084</number>
/ 
<quantity box="[883,1001,260,284]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" unit="mm" value="0.048">0.048 mm</quantity>
. Rudimentary seminal capsule visible. Sternite 
<number box="[244,258,296,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="8.0">8</number>
with v-shaped caudomedian excavation, caudal lobes distinct. Cerci very short.
</paragraph>
